mbt
------------------------------------------
MBT is a memory-based tagger-generator and tagger in one. The tagger-generator
part can generate a sequence tagger on the basis of a training set of tagged
sequences; the tagger part can tag new sequences. MBT can, for instance, be
used to generate part-of-speech taggers or chunkers for natural language
processing. It has also been used for named-entity recognition, information
extraction in domain-specific texts, and disfluency chunking in transcribed
speech.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libgcc1-6.4.0-5
  libgomp1-6.4.0-5
  libmbt-devel-3.3.1-1bl1
  libmbt1-3.3.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-5
  libticcutils3-0.17-1bl1
  libtimbl-devel-6.4.11-1bl1
  libtimbl4-6.4.11-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.30.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://languagemachines.github.io/mbt

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/LanguageMachines/mbt/archive/v3.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mbt-3.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mbt-3.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mbt-3.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mbt-3.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmbt1-3.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmbt-devel-3.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mbt)
  /usr/bin/mbt.exe
  /usr/bin/mbtg.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mbt.README
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/TODO
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/examples/eindh.data
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/examples/eindh.test
  /usr/share/doc/mbt/examples/simpletest.setting
  /usr/share/man/man1/mbt.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/mbtg.1.gz

(libmbt1)
  /usr/bin/cygmbt-1.dll

(libmbt-devel)
  /usr/include/mbt/Logging.h
  /usr/include/mbt/MbtAPI.h
  /usr/include/mbt/Pattern.h
  /usr/include/mbt/Sentence.h
  /usr/include/mbt/TagLex.h
  /usr/include/mbt/Tagger.h
  /usr/lib/libmbt.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/mbt.pc

